from IPython.display import HTML
HTML('''<script>  
code_show=true; 
function code_toggle() {
  if (code_show){
    $(\'div.input\').hide();
  } else {
    $(\'div.input\').show();
  }
  code_show = !code_show
}  
$( document ).ready(code_toggle);
</script>
  <form action="javascript:code_toggle()">
    <input type="submit" value="Click here to toggle on/off the code.">
 </form>''')

for i in os.listdir('./data/'):
    y, sr = librosa.load('./data/'+i)
    plt.figure()
    librosa.display.waveplot(y, sr=sr)
    plt.title(i)

In [123]:
path='./data/Recording0013.wav'
y, sr = librosa.load(path, sr=20000, mono=True, offset=1.19, duration=0.25)
melspec = librosa.feature.melspectrogram(y, sr, n_fft=1024, hop_length=512, n_mels=128)
logmelspec = librosa.power_to_db(melspec) 
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
librosa.display.specshow(logmelspec,y_axis='mel', x_axis='time')
plt.colorbar()
plt.title('Mel spectrogram'+path)
plt.tight_layout()
